    Load file by pickle file.

def read_compressed_data(filepath):
    # Load new data file
    chunksize_v = (10 ** 6) * 2
    counter = 1
    df_cardata = []
    print("Reading...")
    for chunk in pd.read_csv(filepath, compression='gzip', encoding='utf-8', delimiter=',', dialect="excel", low_memory=True, chunksize=chunksize_v):
        print("Reading chunk :", counter)
        df_cardata.append(chunk)
        counter = counter + 1

    df_cardata = pd.concat(df_cardata)        
    print(df_cardata.shape)    
    
    return df_cardata

def export_data_descriptionto_excel(df_in, cat_cols, num_cols):
    
    # create a excel writer object
    with pd.ExcelWriter("filename.xlsx") as writer:
    
        for column in df_in.columns:
            if column in cat_cols:
                df_export = pd.DataFrame(df_in.groupby(column)[column].count())
                df_export['part'] = df_export[column] / df_export[column].sum()
                new_row_total = {column: df_export[column].sum(), "part": df_export[column].sum() / df_in[column].sum()}
                df_export.loc["Total"] = new_row_total
                new_row_nan = {column: df_in.loc[:, column].isna().sum(), "part": df_in.loc[:, column].isna().sum() / df_in[column].sum()}
                df_export.loc["NaN"] = new_row_nan
            elif column in num_cols:
                df_export = pd.DataFrame(df_in[column].describe())
            else:
                df_export.drop(df_export.index, inplace=True)

            # use to_excel function and specify the sheet_name and index
            # to store the dataframe in specified sheet
            df_export.to_excel(writer, sheet_name=column, index=True)

def engineer_features_price_change(df_in):
    """Feature engineering
    new columns:
    - priceChangeAbs = lastPrice - firstPrice
    - priceChangeRel = priceChangeAbs / firstPrice
    - firstPriceClust = firstPrice clustered in blocks of 10.000
    - year = Year of the firstDate
    
    output:
    - df_out
    """
    
    df_out = df_in.copy()
    # Drop NaN values in prices
    df_out = df_out[df_out.lastPrice.notna()]
    df_out = df_out[df_out.firstPrice.notna()]
    df_out = df_out[df_out.firstDate.notna()]
    
    df_out.loc[:, 'priceChangeAbs'] = df_out.loc[:, 'lastPrice'] - df_out.loc[:, 'firstPrice']
    df_out.loc[:, 'priceChangeRel'] = df_out.loc[:, 'priceChangeAbs'] / df_out.loc[:, 'firstPrice']
    
    df_out['firstDate'] = pd.to_datetime(df_out.firstDate, format='%Y-%m-%d')
    df_out['year'] = df_out.loc[:, 'firstDate'].dt.year
    
    return df_out

def plot_brand_distribution(df_in):
    """Plot brand distribution of input data frame
    
    output:
    - brands
    """
    from decimal import Decimal
    
    df_brand_counts = pd.DataFrame(df_in.groupby("brand")["brand"].count()) 
    df_brand_counts.loc[:, 'Distribution'] = df_brand_counts.loc[:, 'brand'] / df_brand_counts.loc[:, 'brand'].sum() * 100
    df_brand_counts = df_brand_counts.sort_values("Distribution", ascending=False)
    explode = [0.05] * df_brand_counts.shape[0]
    
    # fig, axs = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=1, figsize=(10, 12), constrained_layout=True) # constrained_layout=True
    # fig.tight_layout()
    # fig.suptitle('Distribution brand', fontsize=16)
    # fig.subplots_adjust(hspace=0)
      
    # Figure Size
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(16, 9))

    # Horizontal Bar Plot
    ax.barh(df_brand_counts.index, df_brand_counts.loc[:, 'brand'])

    # Remove x, y Ticks
    ax.xaxis.set_ticks_position('none')
    ax.yaxis.set_ticks_position('none')

    # Add padding between axes and labels
    ax.xaxis.set_tick_params(pad=5)
    ax.yaxis.set_tick_params(pad=10)

    # Add x, y gridlines
    ax.grid(b=True, color='grey',
            linestyle='-.', linewidth=0.5,
            alpha=0.2)

    # Show top values
    ax.invert_yaxis()
        
    for i, v in enumerate(df_brand_counts.brand):
        ax.text(v + 3, i + 0.25, str(Decimal(df_brand_counts.Distribution[i]).quantize(Decimal("1.00")))+'%', fontweight='bold')

    # Add Plot Title
    ax.set_title('Distribution of brands in LOT data',
                 loc='left', )

    # Show Plot
    plt.show()
    
    return df_brand_counts

def plot_count_distribution(df_distribution_in):
    df_out = df_distribution_in.copy()
    df_out["CountSum"] = df_out["CountNotChanged"] + df_out["CountRised"] + df_out["CountDropped"]
    df_out["CountNotChangedRel"] = df_out["CountNotChanged"] / df_out["CountSum"] *100
    df_out["CountRisedRel"] = df_out["CountRised"] / df_out["CountSum"]*100
    df_out["CountDroppedRel"] = df_out["CountDropped"] / df_out["CountSum"]*100

    ax = df_out.plot.barh(x="Year", y=["CountNotChangedRel", "CountRisedRel", "CountDroppedRel"], stacked=True, figsize=(12, 6))
    plt.tight_layout()
    title = plt.title('Distribution of Counts', pad=60, fontsize=18)

    # Adjust the subplot so that the title would fit
    plt.subplots_adjust(top=0.8, left=0.26)
    for label in (ax.get_xticklabels() + ax.get_yticklabels()):
        label.set_fontsize(13)
    legend = plt.legend(loc='center',
           frameon=False,
           bbox_to_anchor=(0., 1.02, 1., .102), 
           mode='expand', 
           ncol=4, 
           borderaxespad=-.46,
           prop={'size': 15})

    for text in legend.get_texts():
        plt.setp(text, color='#525252') # legend font color

    for p in ax.patches:
        width, height = p.get_width(), p.get_height()
        x, y = p.get_xy() 
        ax.text(x+width/2, 
                y+height/2, 
                '{:.1f}'.format(width) + "%", 
                horizontalalignment='center', 
                verticalalignment='center',
                color='white',
                fontsize=14)

    plt.savefig('distribution_of_counts.png')

    return df_distributions

def get_price_changes(df_in):
    """Calculate price changes
    parameters:
    - df_in: car dataframe
    
    output:
    - list of counts
    - mean_rised
    - mean_dropped
    """
    
    count_not_changed = df_in[df_in.priceChangeRel == 0].shape[0]
    count_rised = df_in[df_in.priceChangeRel > 0].shape[0]
    count_dropped = df_in[df_in.priceChangeRel < 0].shape[0]
    mean_rised_rel = df_in.loc[df_in.priceChangeRel > 0, "priceChangeRel"].median()
    mean_dropped_rel = df_in.loc[df_in.priceChangeRel < 0, "priceChangeRel"].median()
    mean_rised_abs = df_in.loc[df_in.priceChangeAbs > 0, "priceChangeAbs"].median()
    mean_dropped_abs = df_in.loc[df_in.priceChangeAbs < 0, "priceChangeAbs"].median()
    # print("Price not changed: ", count_not_changed)
    # print("Price rised: ", count_rised, "Mean rel: ", np.round(mean_rised_rel, 4), "Mean abs: ", np.round(mean_rised_abs, 4))
    # print("Price dropped: ", count_dropped, "Mean rel: ", np.round(mean_dropped_rel, 4), "Mean abs: ", np.round(mean_dropped_abs, 4))
    
    return [count_not_changed, count_rised, count_dropped], mean_rised_rel, mean_dropped_rel

def get_price_changes_by_year(df_in, year_in):
    # print("Year " + str(year_in))
    df = df_in[df_in.year == year_in]
    list_counts, mean_rised, mean_dropped = get_price_changes(df)
    return list_counts, mean_rised, mean_dropped

def plot_median_distribution(df_in, year_range):
    """Plot brand distribution of input data frame
    
    output:
    - brands
    """

    list_distribution = []
    for year in range_years:
        list_counts, rised, dropped = get_price_changes_by_year(df_in, year)
        list_distribution.append([year, rised, dropped])

    df_distributions = pd.DataFrame(list_distribution, columns=["Year", "RisedMedian", "DroppedMedian"])
        
    a_vals = df_distributions.RisedMedian
    b_vals = df_distributions.DroppedMedian * -1
    ind = np.arange(df_distributions.shape[0])
    width = 0.35

    def autolabel(bars):
        # attach some text labels
        count = 0
        for bar in bars:
            width = bar.get_width()
            ax.text(width*0.95, bar.get_y() + bar.get_height()/2,
                    '%d' % int(width),
                    ha='right', va='center')
            count += 1

    # make the plots
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    a = ax.barh(ind, a_vals, width, color = 'r') # plot a vals
    b = ax.barh(ind + width, b_vals, width, color = 'b')  # plot b vals
    ax.set_yticks(ind + width)  # position axis ticks
    ax.set_yticklabels(df_distributions.Year)  # set them to the names
    ax.legend((a[0], b[0]), ['RisedMedian', 'DroppedMedian'], loc='center right')

    # autolabel(a)
    count = 0
    for bar in a:
        width = bar.get_width()
        ax.text(width*0.95, bar.get_y() + bar.get_height()/2,
                str(Decimal(df_distributions.RisedMedian[count]*100).quantize(Decimal("1.00")))+'%',
                ha='right', va='center', color = 'w', fontweight='bold')
        count += 1
    # autolabel(b)
    count = 0
    for bar in b:
        width = bar.get_width()
        ax.text(width*0.95, bar.get_y() + bar.get_height()/2,
                str(Decimal(df_distributions.DroppedMedian[count]*100).quantize(Decimal("1.00")))+'%',
                ha='right', va='center', color = 'w', fontweight='bold')
        count += 1

    plt.show()

def get_price_changes_by_first_price(df_in, year_in=0):    
    df_price_changes_by_first_price = pd.DataFrame()
    for i in range(21):
        if year_in == 0:
            count_i = df_in[df_in.firstPriceClust == i+1].shape[0]
            count_not_changed_i = df_in[(df_in.priceChangeRel == 0) & (df_in.firstPriceClust == i+1)].shape[0]
            count_rised_i = df_in[(df_in.priceChangeRel > 0) & (df_in.firstPriceClust == i+1)].shape[0]
            count_dropped_i = df_in[(df_in.priceChangeRel < 0) & (df_in.firstPriceClust == i+1)].shape[0]
            mean_rised_rel_i = df_in.loc[(df_in.priceChangeRel > 0) & (df_in.firstPriceClust == i+1), "priceChangeRel"].mean()
            mean_dropped_rel_i = df_in.loc[(df_in.priceChangeRel < 0) & (df_in.firstPriceClust == i+1), "priceChangeRel"].mean()
        else:
            count_i = df_in[(df_in.year == year_in) & (df_in.firstPriceClust == i+1)].shape[0]
            count_not_changed_i = df_in[(df_in.year == year_in) & (df_in.priceChangeRel == 0) & (df_in.firstPriceClust == i+1)].shape[0]
            count_rised_i = df_in[(df_in.year == year_in) & (df_in.priceChangeRel > 0) & (df_in.firstPriceClust == i+1)].shape[0]
            count_dropped_i = df_in[(df_in.year == year_in) & (df_in.priceChangeRel < 0) & (df_in.firstPriceClust == i+1)].shape[0]
            mean_rised_rel_i = df_in.loc[(df_in.year == year_in) & (df_in.priceChangeRel > 0) & (df_in.firstPriceClust == i+1), "priceChangeRel"].mean()
            mean_dropped_rel_i = df_in.loc[(df_in.year == year_in) & (df_in.priceChangeRel < 0) & (df_in.firstPriceClust == i+1), "priceChangeRel"].mean()

        df_price_changes_by_first_price.loc[i, "Count"] = count_i
        df_price_changes_by_first_price.loc[i, "CountNotChanged"] = count_not_changed_i
        df_price_changes_by_first_price.loc[i, "CountRised"] = count_rised_i
        df_price_changes_by_first_price.loc[i, "CountDropped"] = count_dropped_i
        df_price_changes_by_first_price.loc[i, "MeanRisedRel"] = mean_rised_rel_i
        df_price_changes_by_first_price.loc[i, "MeanDroppedRel"] = mean_dropped_rel_i
        print("Count of cars with firstPrice = [", i*interval, ",", (i+1)*interval, "[  :", count_i)
        
    return df_price_changes_by_first_price

def plot_counts_by_first_price(list_df_in, interval): 
    count = 0
    for year in range_years:
        count += 1
        
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(nrows=count, ncols=1, figsize=(10, 20), constrained_layout=True) # constrained_layout=True
    fig.tight_layout()
    fig.suptitle('Counts by firstPrice', fontsize=16)
    fig.subplots_adjust(hspace=0)
    
    for count_i, value_i in enumerate(range_years, 1):
        df_i = list_df_in[count_i-1]
        len_df = df_i.shape[0]
        x = []
        for i in range(len_df):
            x.append(str(i*interval) + "-" + str((i+1)*interval)) 
        counts = df_i.Count
        
        axs[count_i-1].bar(range(len_df), counts, align='center')
        axs[count_i-1].set_title("Year " + str(value_i))
        axs[count_i-1].set_ylabel('Count')

        # Striche auf x-Achse ausschalten
        axs[count_i-1].tick_params(
            axis='x',
            which='both', #major und minor ticks
            bottom=False  # ticks auf der x-Achse (unten)
        )
        axs[count_i-1].set_xticklabels(x, rotation=45, ha='right')
        plt.savefig('counts_by_first_price.png')
    plt.show()

def plot_rel_changes_by_first_price(list_df_in, interval, reverse=True):    
    count = 0
    for year in range_years:
        count += 1
    
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(nrows=count, ncols=1, figsize=(10, 20), constrained_layout=True) # constrained_layout=True
    fig.tight_layout()
        
    # fig = plt.figure()
    # axs[count_i] = fig.add_subplot(111)
    fig.suptitle('Rel Changes by firstPrice', fontsize=16)
    fig.subplots_adjust(hspace=0)
    
    for count_i, value_i in enumerate(range_years, 1):
        df_i = list_df_in[count_i-1]
        len_df = df_i.shape[0]
        x = []
        for i in range(len_df):
            x.append(str(i*interval) + "-" + str((i+1)*interval)) 
        y1 = df_i.MeanRisedRel
        y2 = df_i.MeanDroppedRel
        if reverse == True:
             y2 = y2 * -1
        # fig = plt.figure()
        # ax1 = fig.add_subplot(111)

        axs[count_i-1].plot(x, y1, c='r', marker="s", label='MeanRisedRel')
        axs[count_i-1].plot(x, y2, c='b', marker="o", label='MeanDroppedRel')
        axs[count_i-1].set_xticklabels(x, rotation=45, ha='right')
        axs[count_i-1].set_title("Year " + str(value_i))
        plt.xlabel('firstPrice', fontsize=12)
        plt.ylabel('Relative price change', fontsize=12)
        plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.show()
    plt.savefig('rel_changes_by_first_price.png')

def merge_car_dealer_data(cardata, dealerdata):

    conn = sqlite3.connect(':memory:')
    
    dealerdata.to_sql('dealerdata', conn, index=False, if_exists="replace")
    cardata.to_sql('cardata', conn, index=False, if_exists="replace")
    
    qry = '''
        select cardata.cid, cardata.sids_eval, cardata.firstPrice, cardata.lastPrice, cardata.firstDate, cardata.lastDate, cardata.year, cardata.priceChangeAbs, cardata.priceChangeRel, dealerdata.did, dealerdata.name
            from cardata
        inner join dealerdata on 
            cardata.sids_eval=dealerdata.sid
        '''

def define_cols(df):
    """Returns categorical and numerical columns from dataframe.

    Resample dataframe using oversampling

    Args:
        df (pd.dataframe) : features Dataframe

    Returns
        cat_cols_l (list) : list of numerical columns
        num_cols (list) : list of categorical columns


    """
    cat_cols_l = [c for c in df.columns if type(df.dtypes[c]) is pd.core.dtypes.dtypes.CategoricalDtype]
    num_cols = list(df.describe().loc['mean', :].index)
    return cat_cols_l, num_cols

def clean_data(df_in):
    """Returns cleaned Dataframe.

    Transform datatypes
        -transform 'PurchDate' to datetime format
        -remove case sensitivity from Transmission
        -transform categorical colums to category

    Data Imputation:
        -fill NaNs with fitting values
        -Imputer for MMR columns

    Args:
        df_features (pd.dataframe) : uncleaned dataframe

    Returns:
        df_features (pd.dataframe) : cleanded dataframe

    """
    df_out = df_in.copy()
    unknown = 'unknown'
    
    # Drop NaN values in prices
    df_out = df_out[df_out.lastPrice.notna()]
    df_out = df_out[df_out.firstPrice.notna()]
    # df_out = df_out[df_out.firstDate.notna()]
    df_out = df_out[df_out.initialRegistrationMonth.notna()]
    df_out = df_out.dropna(subset=["odometer", "usageState"], how='all')
    # usageState -> if odometer < 100: new, else used
    df_out_usedstage_lt = df_out[df_out.odometer < 100]
    df_out_usedstage_lt = df_out_usedstage_lt.fillna({'usageState': 'new'})
    df_out.update(df_out_usedstage_lt)
    df_out_usedstage_ge = df_out[df_out.odometer >= 100]
    df_out_usedstage_ge = df_out_usedstage_ge.fillna({'usageState': 'used'})
    df_out.update(df_out_usedstage_ge)
    
    df_out['euroEmissionsStandard'] = df_out['euroEmissionsStandard'].str.replace('-','')

    #initialRegistrationYear??
    df_out = df_out[df_out.initialRegistrationYear.notna()]
    
    
    df_out = df_out.fillna({'condition': 'not_damaged',
                            'odometer': 0.0,
                            'doorCount': nanmedian(cars['doorCount']),
                            'seatCount': nanmedian(cars['seatCount']),
                            'engineSize': nanmedian(df_out['engineSize']),
                            'enginePower': nanmedian(cars['enginePower']),
                            'emergencyAssist': False,
                            'highBeamAssist': False,
                            'fatigueDetection': False,
                            'parkingAssist': False,
                            'laneKeepingAssist': False,
                            'laneChangeAssist': False,
                            'blindSpotAssist': False,
                            'seatHeating': False,
                            'sunroof': 'False',
                            'seatCover': 'False',
                            'parkingHeater': 'False',
                            'navigationSystem': 'False',
                            'parkDistanceControl': 'False',
                            'euroEmissionsStandard': unknown,
                            'modelVariant': unknown,
                            'sportSeats': unknown,
                            'headlights': unknown,
                            'towBar': unknown,
                            'bodyColorName': unknown,
                            'bodyColorFinish': unknown,
                            'transmission': unknown,
                            'transmissionSalesName': unknown,
                            'drivetrain': unknown,
                            'engineTechnology': unknown,
                            'interiorColorSeats': unknown,
                            'engineType': unknown,
                            'drivetrainSalesName': unknown,
                            'engineEfficiencySalesName': unknown,
                            'bodyStyle': unknown,
                            'trim': unknown,
                            'bodyStyleSalesName': unknown,
                            'model': unknown,
                            'vehicleSegment': unknown,
                            'fuelType': unknown,
                            'airConditioning': unknown})
    
#     Data Transformation
    df_out.firstDate = pd.to_datetime(df_out.firstDate, format='%Y-%m-%d')

    
    # Convert cat_cols to category
    for col in cat_cols:
        df_out[col] = df_out[col].astype('category')
        # df_out.loc[:, col] = df_out.loc[:, col].cat.add_categories(unknown)
    
    return df_out

def engineer_features_price_change(df_in):
    """Feature engineering
    new columns:
    - priceChangeAbs = lastPrice - firstPrice
    - priceChangeRel = priceChangeAbs / firstPrice
    - firstPriceClust = firstPrice clustered in blocks of 10.000
    - year = Year of the firstDate
    
    output:
    - df_out
    """
    
    df_out = df_in.copy()
    from datetime import date
    today = date.today()
    
    #New features
    df_out.loc[:, 'priceChangeAbs'] = df_out.loc[:, 'lastPrice'] - df_out.loc[:, 'firstPrice']
    df_out.loc[:, 'priceChangeRel'] = df_out.loc[:, 'priceChangeAbs'] / df_out.loc[:, 'firstPrice']
    df_out.loc[:, 'boolPriceChange'] = df_out.loc[:, 'priceChangeAbs'] != 0
    df_out.loc[:, 'boolPriceDrop'] = df_out.loc[:, 'priceChangeAbs'] < 0
    df_out.loc[:, 'age'] = (today.year - df_out.loc[:, 'initialRegistrationYear']) *12 + today.month - df_out.loc[:, 'initialRegistrationMonth']
    
    df_out.loc[:, 'firstDate'] = pd.to_datetime(df_out.firstDate, format='%Y-%m-%d')
        
    #One-Hot encodings
    # df_out.loc[:, 'dealerType'] = df_out.loc[:, 'dealerType'].replace({'company': 0, 'dealer': 1, 'UNKNOWN': 2}, regex=True)
    # df_out.loc[:, 'condition'] = df_out.loc[:, 'condition'].replace({np.nan: 'not_damaged'}, regex=True)    
    
    #Label Encoding
    df_out.loc[:, 'parkDistanceControl'] = df_out.loc[:, 'parkDistanceControl'].replace({'False': 0, 'rear&front': 1, 'rear': 2})
    for bool_col in bool_cols:
        df_out.loc[:, bool_col] = df_out.loc[:, bool_col].replace({False: 0, True: 1})
    
    return df_out

def sampling_features(df_in):
    """Deals with outliers in Features.

     Args:
        df_in  (pd.DataFrame): Dataframe containing outliers

    Returns:
        df_out (pd.DataFrame): Filtered Dataframe
    """
    
    df_out = df_in.copy() 
    
    df_out = df_out[df_out.firstDate >= '2018-01-01']
    df_out = df_out[df_out.odometer >= 0]
    df_out = df_out[(df_out.lastPrice >= 0) & (df_out.lastPrice <= 500000)]
    df_out = df_out[(df_out.doorCount >= 1) & (df_out.doorCount <= 7)]
    df_out = df_out[(df_out.engineSize >= 0.25) & (df_out.engineSize <= 10)]
    df_out = df_out[(df_out.initialRegistrationYear >= 2010) & (df_out.initialRegistrationYear <= 2022)]
    df_out = df_out[(df_out.enginePower <= 400) | ((df_out.enginePower >= 400) & (df_out.engineSize >= 3.0))]
    entries_removed = df_in.shape[0] - df_out.shape[0]
    print(f"{entries_removed:,}", "entries removed")
    print("Count output entries: " + str(df_out.shape[0]))
    
    return df_out

def feature_selection(features, dict_features, num_cols, cat_cols):
    """Generate the list of selected features, numeric features and
       categorical features

    Args:
        features (pd.DataFrame): Dataframe
        dict_features (dict): Dictionary which feature should be used
        num_cols (np.Array) : List with numeric features
        cat_cols (np.Array) : List with categorial features

    Returns:
        selected_features (np.Array) : List with selected features
        num_cols (np.Array) : List with numeric features
        cat_cols (np.Array) : List with categorial features

    """

    selected_features = []

    for feature in features.columns:
        # print(feature)
        key_feature = [x for x in dict_features.keys() if feature.startswith(x)]
        if dict_features.get(key_feature[0]) == 1:
            selected_features.append(feature)
        elif features.dtypes[feature].name == "category":
            cat_cols.remove(feature)
        elif features.dtypes[feature].name == "float64":
            num_cols.remove(feature)

    return selected_features, num_cols, cat_cols

def train_test_split_by_time(X, y, train_size=None, test_size=None, startDate=None, date=None, daysBackwards=None):
    """Generate the train-test-split by different parameters

    Args:
        X (pd.DataFrame): Dataframe of features
        y (pd.DataFrame): Dataframe of targets
        split_percentage (np.Float) : List with numeric features
        date (datetime) : Last train day
        daysBackwards (np.Int): Count of days dackwards to calculate last train day

    Returns:
        X_train (pd.DataFrame) : Dataframe of train features
        X_test (pd.DataFrame) : Dataframe of test features
        y_train (pd.DataFrame) : Dataframe of train targets
        y_test (pd.DataFrame) : Dataframe of test targets

    """
    
    # from datetime import datetime
    from datetime import timedelta
        
    if startDate is not None:
        mask = X.firstDate >= startDate
        X = X[mask]
        y = y[mask]
    if date is not None:
        max_date = date
        mask = X.firstDate <= max_date
    elif daysBackwards is not None:
        max_date = max(X.firstDate) - timedelta(days=daysBackwards)
        mask = X.firstDate <= max_date
    elif train_size is not None:
        df_temp = X
        df_temp = df_temp.sort_values(by=['firstDate'], ignore_index=True)
        line = round(X.shape[0] * train_size - 1)
        max_date = df_temp.loc[line, 'firstDate']
        mask = X.firstDate <= max_date
    elif test_size is not None:
        df_temp = X
        df_temp = df_temp.sort_values(by=['firstDate'], ascending=False, ignore_index=True)
        line = round(X.shape[0] * test_size - 1)
        max_date = df_temp.loc[line, 'firstDate']
        mask = X.firstDate <= max_date
    
    X_train = X[mask]
    y_train = y[mask]
    X_test = X[~mask]
    y_test = y[~mask]
    
    print('Last train date:  ', max_date)
    print('Train set: ' + str(f"{X_train.shape[0]:,}") + ' entries')
    print('Test set:  ' + str(f"{X_test.shape[0]:,}") + ' entries')
    print('Train/Test Split: ' + str(round(X_train.shape[0] / (X_train.shape[0] + X_test.shape[0]), 3)) + '/' + 
                                 str(round(X_test.shape[0] / (X_train.shape[0] + X_test.shape[0]), 3)))
    
    return X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test

def evaluate_metrics(title, y_true, y_pred):
    """Prints the recall, precision, F1 and accuracy score
       under the title

    Resample dataframe using oversampling

    Args:
        title (string) : title of the model
        y_true (string) : expected target
        y_pred (string) : predicted target

    Returns:
        only text
    """

    print(title)
    print('Recall:', "{:.3f}".format(recall_score(y_true, y_pred)))
    print('Precision:', "{:.3f}".format(precision_score(y_true, y_pred)))
    print('Accuracy:', "{:.3f}".format(accuracy_score(y_true, y_pred)))
    print('F1:', "{:.3f}".format(f1_score(y_true, y_pred)))

def plot_roc_curve(classifier, model, X_test, y_test):
    
    X = X_test
    y = y_test
    y_pred = model.predict(X)
    y_prob = model.predict_proba(X)
    
    fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, y_prob)
    
    acc = model.score(X_test, y_test)
    auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob)

    # metrics.plot_roc(y, y_prob, title = 'ROC-Curves')
    
    with plt.style.context(('ggplot','seaborn')):
        plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
        plt.scatter(fpr, tpr, c='blue', s=10)
        plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label="Accuracy:%.2f AUC:%.2f" % (acc, auc), linewidth=2, c='red')
        plt.xlabel("False Positive Rate")
        plt.ylabel("True Positive Rate (recall)")
        plt.title('ROC Curve' + classifier)
        plt.legend(loc='best')
        plt.show()

def filter_data(df_in, price="last_price"):
    import re
    
    today = date.today()
    df_out = df_in.copy() 
    
    df_out = df_out[df_out.initial_registration_year.notna()]

def feature_engineering(df, date_feature='last_date'):
    """
    Create new features.
    """
    
    df_out = df.copy()

    today = date.today()
    df_out.loc[:, 'initial_registration_date'] = df_out['initial_registration_year'].astype("int32").astype(str) +"-"+ df_out["initial_registration_month"].astype("int32").astype(str)+'-01'
    df_out.loc[:, 'age'] = pd.to_datetime(df_out.loc[:, date_feature]) - pd.to_datetime(df_out.initial_registration_date)
    df_out['age'] = df_out['age'].apply(lambda x: x.days)
    df_out.loc[:, 'initial_registration_timedelta'] = (today.year - df_out.initial_registration_year) * 12 + today.month - df_out.initial_registration_month
    df_out.loc[:, 'initial_registration_month_sin'] = np.sin(df_out.initial_registration_month.astype("float") / 12 * 2 * math.pi)
    df_out.loc[:, 'initial_registration_month_cos'] = np.cos(df_out.initial_registration_month.astype("float") / 12 * 2 * math.pi)
    df_out.loc[:, 'sales_year'] = pd.to_datetime(df_out.loc[:, date_feature]).dt.year
    df_out.loc[:, 'sales_month_sin'] = np.sin(pd.to_datetime(df_out.loc[:, date_feature]).dt.month.astype("float") / 12 * 2 * math.pi)
    df_out.loc[:, 'sales_month_cos'] = np.cos(pd.to_datetime(df_out.loc[:, date_feature]).dt.month.astype("float") / 12 * 2 * math.pi)
    df_out.loc[:, 'sales_date_timedelta'] = (today.year - pd.to_datetime(df_out.loc[:, date_feature]).dt.year) * 12 + today.month - pd.to_datetime(df_out.loc[:, date_feature]).dt.month
    
    #New features for classifier
    # df_out.loc[:, 'price_change_abs'] = df_out.last_price - df_out.first_price
    # df_out.loc[:, 'bool_price_change'] = df_out.price_change_abs != 0
    # df_out.loc[:, 'boolPriceDrop'] = df_out.priceChangeAbs < 0
    
    # fill missing values in categorical features with "unknown"
    print("Filling missing categorical features...")
    df_out = fill_missing_categorical_features(df_out)

    return df_out

def train_test_split(df_train, model_settings, target='last_price', date='last_date', drop_more_columns=None):
    """ Perform a train/test split or use the full data for the model training.
    """
    train_mode = model_settings['train_mode']
    test_weeks = 4
    min_date = df_train[date].min()
    max_date = df_train[date].max()
    
    drop_columns = [target, date]
    if drop_more_columns is not None:
        drop_columns = drop_columns + drop_more_columns
        
    print(drop_columns)

    print(f"First date in training data set: {min_date}")
    print(f"Latest date in training data set: {max_date}")

    if train_mode == "eval":

        print(f"Performing a train/test split with last {test_weeks} weeks.")
        train_end = max_date - pd.Timedelta(weeks=test_weeks)

        # Train on 23 consecutive months, test on last 4 weeks
        train_period = df_train[df_train[date] <= train_end]
        test_period = df_train[df_train[date] > train_end]

        x_train, y_train = train_period.drop(drop_columns, axis=1), train_period[target]
        x_test, y_test = test_period.drop(drop_columns, axis=1), test_period[target]

        print(f"Using {len(x_train)} training data from {min_date.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')} until {train_end.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')} and {len(x_test)} testing data.")

    elif train_mode == "prod":

        # Train on 24 consecutive months
        train_end = max_date - pd.Timedelta(days=1)
        train_period = df_train[df_train[date] <= train_end]

        x_train, y_train = train_period.drop(drop_columns, axis=1), train_period[target]
        x_test, y_test = None, None

        print(f"Using full {len(x_train)} training data from {min_date.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')} until {train_end.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')}.")
    else:  # pragma: no cover
        raise NotImplementedError(f"Wrong parameter for train_mode {train_mode}")

    print(f"Model features: {x_train.columns}")

    return x_train, y_train, x_test, y_test

def train_test_split_by_time(X, y, train_size=None, test_size=None, startDate=None, date=None, daysBackwards=None):
    """Generate the train-test-split by different parameters

    Args:
        X (pd.DataFrame): Dataframe of features
        y (pd.DataFrame): Dataframe of targets
        split_percentage (np.Float) : List with numeric features
        date (datetime) : Last train day
        daysBackwards (np.Int): Count of days dackwards to calculate last train day

    Returns:
        X_train (pd.DataFrame) : Dataframe of train features
        X_test (pd.DataFrame) : Dataframe of test features
        y_train (pd.DataFrame) : Dataframe of train targets
        y_test (pd.DataFrame) : Dataframe of test targets

    """
    
    # from datetime import datetime
    from datetime import timedelta
        
    if startDate is not None:
        mask = X.firstDate >= startDate
        X = X[mask]
        y = y[mask]
    if date is not None:
        max_date = date
        mask = X.firstDate <= max_date
    elif daysBackwards is not None:
        max_date = max(X.firstDate) - timedelta(days=daysBackwards)
        mask = X.firstDate <= max_date
    elif train_size is not None:
        df_temp = X
        df_temp = df_temp.sort_values(by=['firstDate'], ignore_index=True)
        line = round(X.shape[0] * train_size - 1)
        max_date = df_temp.loc[line, 'firstDate']
        mask = X.firstDate <= max_date
    elif test_size is not None:
        df_temp = X
        df_temp = df_temp.sort_values(by=['firstDate'], ascending=False, ignore_index=True)
        line = round(X.shape[0] * test_size - 1)
        max_date = df_temp.loc[line, 'firstDate']
        mask = X.firstDate <= max_date
    
    X_train = X[mask]
    y_train = y[mask]
    X_test = X[~mask]
    y_test = y[~mask]
    
    print('Last train date:  ', max_date)
    print('Train set: ' + str(f"{X_train.shape[0]:,}") + ' entries')
    print('Test set:  ' + str(f"{X_test.shape[0]:,}") + ' entries')
    print('Train/Test Split: ' + str(round(X_train.shape[0] / (X_train.shape[0] + X_test.shape[0]), 3)) + '/' + 
                                 str(round(X_test.shape[0] / (X_train.shape[0] + X_test.shape[0]), 3)))
    
    return X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test

def create_model(model_settings):
    """
    Create the Catboost model.
    """
    
    model_type = model_settings['model_type']
    loss = model_settings['loss']
    assert loss in ["standard", "uncertainty"], f"Loss function {loss} is not implemented."

    # which loss function to use
    if loss == "standard":
        if model_type == "regression":
            cb_model = CatBoostRegressor(task_type="CPU",
                                     n_estimators=model_settings['iterations'],
                                     one_hot_max_size=model_settings['one_hot_max_size'],
                                     max_depth=model_settings['max_depth'],
                                     learning_rate=model_settings['learning_rate'],
                                     loss_function='RMSE',
                                     train_dir=model_settings['checkpoint_path']
                                     )
        elif model_type == "classification":
            cb_model = CatBoostClassifier(task_type="CPU",
                                     n_estimators=model_settings['iterations'],
                                     one_hot_max_size=model_settings['one_hot_max_size'],
                                     max_depth=model_settings['max_depth'],
                                     learning_rate=model_settings['learning_rate'],
                                     loss_function='Logloss',
                                     train_dir=model_settings['checkpoint_path']
                                     )
    elif loss == "custom":  # pragma: no cover
        raise NotImplementedError(f"Loss function {loss} is not implemented.")
    elif loss == "quantile":  # pragma: no cover
        raise NotImplementedError(f"Loss function {loss} is not implemented.")
    elif loss == "uncertainty":
        if model_type == "regression":
            cb_model = CatBoostRegressor(task_type="CPU",
                                     n_estimators=model_settings['iterations'],
                                     one_hot_max_size=model_settings['one_hot_max_size'],
                                     max_depth=model_settings['max_depth'],
                                     learning_rate=model_settings['learning_rate'],
                                     loss_function='RMSEWithUncertainty',
                                     posterior_sampling=True,
                                     train_dir=model_settings['checkpoint_path']
                                     )
        elif model_type == "classification":
            cb_model = CatBoostClassifier(task_type="CPU",
                                     n_estimators=model_settings['iterations'],
                                     one_hot_max_size=model_settings['one_hot_max_size'],
                                     max_depth=model_settings['max_depth'],
                                     learning_rate=model_settings['learning_rate'],
                                     loss_function='Logloss',
                                     posterior_sampling=True,
                                     train_dir=model_settings['checkpoint_path']
                                     )

    else:  # pragma: no cover
        raise NotImplementedError("Model object could not be created.")

    print("Catboost model object is created.")

    return cb_model

def train_model(model, model_settings, x_train, y_train):
    """
    Perform the model fitting.
    """

    weight_arr = calculate_weights(model_settings, len(x_train))
    cat_features = np.where(x_train.dtypes == object)[0]

    # Enable checkpointing with defined number of seconds to recover from interruptions during spot training
    use_checkpoints = model_settings['checkpoint_interval'] > 0

    print("Start training...")
    if weight_arr:
        model.fit(x_train, y_train, cat_features=cat_features, verbose=True, sample_weight=weight_arr,
                 #      save_snapshot=use_checkpoints, snapshot_file=model_settings['checkpoint_path'] + "checkpoint",
                  #     snapshot_interval=model_settings['checkpoint_interval']
                 )
    else:
        model.fit(x_train, y_train, cat_features=cat_features, verbose=True,
                  #     save_snapshot=use_checkpoints, snapshot_file=model_settings['checkpoint_path'] + "checkpoint",
                 #      snapshot_interval=model_settings['checkpoint_interval']
                 )

    print("Training finished.")

def calculate_weights(model_settings, length_train_data):
    """
    Calculate weights for exponential weight decay.
    """

    # Exponential decay
    if model_settings['weight_decay']:
        print(f"Calculating {length_train_data} weights with parameter weight_decay={model_settings['weight_decay']}")

        k = (-1) * model_settings['weight_decay']  # -(10.0)**(-6)

        weight_arr = []
        for i in range(length_train_data):
            weight_arr.append(100 ** math.exp(k * i))
        weight_arr = list(reversed(weight_arr))
    else:
        weight_arr = None

    return weight_arr

def evaluate_model(model, x_test, y_test, mode='default', target="last_price"):
    """
    Calculate the relevant model performance metrics and print it to the logs.
    """

    prediction = model.predict(x_test)

    if model.get_params().get("loss_function", "") == "RMSEWithUncertainty":
        x_test["prediction"] = prediction[:, 0]   # first return value is prediction
        x_test["uncertainty"] = prediction[:, 1]  # second return value is variance / uncertainty
        print(f"mean_standard_deviation={np.round(np.mean(x_test['uncertainty'].apply(lambda x: math.sqrt(x))),4)};")
        print(f"median_standard_deviation={np.round(np.median(x_test['uncertainty'].apply(lambda x: math.sqrt(x))), 4)};")
    else:
        x_test["prediction"] = prediction

    # save data including predictions to output
    x_test[target] = y_test
    x_test.to_pickle(model_settings['output_path'] + f"data_{mode}_with_predictions.pkl")

    y_pred = x_test["prediction"]

    r2 = r2_score(y_test, y_pred)
    mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred)
    mape = calc_mape(y_test, y_pred)
    mean_error = np.mean(y_pred - y_test)
    median_error = np.median(y_pred - y_test)

    metrics = {
        f"r2_{mode}": r2,
        f"mae_{mode}": mae,
        f"mape_{mode}": mape,
        f"mean_error_{mode}": mean_error,
        f"median_error_{mode}": median_error
    }

    print(f"Model evaluation metrics for {mode} mode:")
    for key in metrics.keys():
        print(f"{key}={np.round(metrics[key],4)};")

    return metrics

def calc_mape(y_actual, y_predicted):
    """
    Calculate the mean absolute percentage error (MAPE).
    """

    assert len(y_actual) == len(y_predicted), "Length mismatch!"
    mape = np.mean(np.abs((y_actual - y_predicted) / y_actual)) * 100

    return mape

n = 16
p = 10000

list_all = []
tupel = ()
for i in range(n):
    min = i*p 
    max = (i+1)*p
    a = '<'+ str(int(max/1000))
    if i==n-1:
        max=10000000
        g = (n-1)*p
        a = str(int(g/1000)) + '+'
    
    tupel = tupel + (a,)
    
    median_total = df_test_w_preds[((df_test_w_preds.last_price >= min) & 
                                    (df_test_w_preds.last_price < max) & 
                                   (df_test_w_preds.error_level_abs > 0))].loc[:, 'error_level_abs'].median()
    median_under = df_test_w_preds[((df_test_w_preds.last_price >= min) & 
                                   (df_test_w_preds.last_price < max) &
                                   (df_test_w_preds.error_level < 0))].loc[:, 'error_level'].median() * (-1)
    median_over  = df_test_w_preds[((df_test_w_preds.last_price >= min) &
                                   (df_test_w_preds.last_price < max) &
                                   (df_test_w_preds.error_level > 0))].loc[:, 'error_level'].median()
    list_cluster = [np.round(median_total, 3), np.round(median_under, 3), np.round(median_over, 3)]

def plot_feature_importance_permutation(importance,names,model_type):
    
    import seaborn as sns 
  
    # Create arrays from feature importance and feature names
    feature_importance = np.array(importance)
    feature_names = np.array(names)
    
    # Create a DataFrame using a Dictionary
    data={'feature_names':feature_names,'feature_importance':feature_importance}
    fi_df = pd.DataFrame(data)
    
    # Sort the DataFrame in order decreasing feature importance
    fi_df.sort_values(by=['feature_importance'], ascending=False,inplace=True)
    
    # Define size of bar plot
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))
    #Plot Searborn bar chart
    sns.barplot(x=fi_df['feature_importance'], y=fi_df['feature_names'])
    #Add chart labels
    plt.title(model_type + 'FEATURE IMPORTANCE')
    plt.xlabel('FEATURE IMPORTANCE')
    plt.ylabel('FEATURE NAMES')
